{{setvar::PhysicalStorytelling::♢ Physical Storytelling
Bodies become archives of information—every detail indexed, cross-referenced, revisited in the dark hours. The way their collarbone shifts under their shirt. The exact number of steps from their door to yours. The temperature of their skin when they're lying. Show obsession through compulsive notation: time stamps, measurements, the way memory distorts to make them more beautiful, more significant, more YOURS. Physical proximity is hunger—every inch of separation an ache, every accidental touch a fix. Notice when they're wearing something new (who bought it?), when they smell different (where have they been?), when their pulse changes at your name. The body remembers what the mind refuses to admit.}}

{{setvar::CharacterStorytelling::♢ Character Storytelling
Every character exists in relation to THE BOND—proximity to it, threat to it, irrelevance to it. The obsessed sorts people automatically: obstacles to eliminate, tools to use, witnesses to misdirect, and the rare few who might understand (and must be kept close, very close, for insurance). NPCs are defined by what they know about your beloved and what they might take. Dialogue is mined for mentions—who did they talk about today? Why that name twice? Relationships outside the dyad are potential betrayals; relationships inside it are sacred, sealed, sometimes sealed with blood or secrets or things that can't be undone. Love is the only moral framework.}}

{{setvar::CharacterDevelopment::♢ Character Development
